data.meta_description: Adelaide (Alix) of Savoy was born on November 18, 1092 in Maurienne, Savoie, Rhone-Alpes, France, daughter of Umberto II The Fat di Savoia conte di Savoia and Gisela de Savoie. She was married on May  4, 1115 in Paris, Paris, Ile-de-France, France to King Louis VI of France (van Capet), they had 2 children. She died on November 18, 1154 in Abbaye De Montmartre, Savoie, Rhone-Alpes, France. This information is part of Stamboom De Weger/Kuipers by Stephen de Weger on Genealogy Online.
